io.smudgr.engine.param

Class Parameter

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.smudgr.engine.param.Parameter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Controllable, ProjectItem, ReflectableType
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BlendParameter, BooleanParameter, NumberParameter, UnivariateParameter

    public abstract class Parameter
extends java.lang.Object
implements Controllable
    The abstract Parameter class defines the generic behavior for interacting with an arbitrarily typed value.

    Parameter implements Controllable, which defines an interface for reacting to input source events.

    See Also:
    Controllable

    • Constructor Detail

      • Parameter

        public Parameter()
        Instantiate a totally empty Parameter, for reflection.

        Because parameters are instantiated in the code and not by loaded states, an empty constructor is required to allow parameter type (i.e. number, boolean, etc) enumeration.

        This could be fixed in the future by instantiating parameters in Parametric instances via super methods instead of directly. The super methods could call setters and return the correct Parameter instance, instead of relying on Parametric implementations to do this properly.

      • getTypeCategoryIdentifier

        public java.lang.String getTypeCategoryIdentifier()
        Description copied from interface: ReflectableType
        This should return a unique identifier of the category of this type.

        The name that this type category is identified to the user with may differ from this identifier. This concept is similar to a 'slug'.

        Implementations of a type should not override this method.

        The String returned by this method should not be changed between versions.

        Specified by:
        getTypeCategoryIdentifier in interface ReflectableType
        Returns:
        String that will enumerate this type category across versions of the application
        See Also:

        public void setValue(java.lang.Object o,
                     ParameterObserver ignoreObserver)
        Set the value of this parameter given a generic Object, with a ParameterObserver specified to be ignored.
